{#
   context_injection.j2
   Injects retrieved ChromaDB chunks into the prompt
   as verified context for the agent to use.
   Addresses reviewer feedback on RAG transparency.
   
   Variables:
   - chunks: list of SourceReference objects
   - query_used: the search query that was run
#}

{% if chunks %}
The following information was retrieved from our 
verified crop disease knowledge base.

Search query used: "{{ query_used }}"

Retrieved context:
{% for chunk in chunks %}

[{{ loop.index }}] Document: {{ chunk.document_name }}
     Chunk ID: {{ chunk.chunk_id }}
     Relevance: {{ chunk.similarity_score }} / 1.0
     {% if chunk.page_number %}
     Page: {{ chunk.page_number }}
     {% endif %}

{{ chunk.chunk_text }}

{% endfor %}

Base your diagnosis primarily on this retrieved 
knowledge combined with the visual evidence.
Always cite the source when referencing this context.

{% else %}
No relevant information was retrieved from the 
disease knowledge base for this query.

This means either:
- The disease is not in our current database
- The image description did not match known patterns
- The retrieval confidence was below the threshold

Clearly state in your response that no database 
context was available and that your diagnosis is 
based solely on visual analysis.
{% endif %}